Description:
The Perfect Paradise
This impressive and spacious 2 bedroom apartment with views to the city skyline is ideal for buyers looking for an abode with a private courtyard, perfect for families, pet owners or those that enjoy outdoor entertaining.
Named after leading Australian painter Arthur Boyd, the Boyd tower exemplifies how the Docklands landscape has developed from humble beginnings.
Located on level 4 of the complex, the residence offers a superb layout. A stylish kitchen with integrated stainless steel appliances and large bench top provides ease of use for the chef, and central entertaining area for guests. Open plan dining and living area leads onto the massive outdoor space, and continuing through a private gate will take you to the manicured common garden area. Spacious main bedroom with ensuite, study alcove and built in robes, and second bedroom also with built in robes, central fully tiled bathroom and separate laundry.
Additional features include: security entrance, floor to ceiling windows, storage cage, secure undercover car park, access to building facilities including swimming pool, gymnasium and BBQ area.
Located within the Free Tram Zone, within walking distance to Southern Cross Station, and with easy Freeway access, you will also be spoilt for choice with local shopping and eateries, including Harbour Town, Spencer Outlet Centre, and Costco. The addition of cinemas and Woolworths to the area to be completed in 2019 will add to the sheer convenience of this ideal location.
Insights: 403/5 Caravel Lane, Docklands VIC 3008 was last sold in 2018 and 275 other 2 bedroom unit in Docklands have recently been sold.

Description:
A One of a Kind Docklands Stunner
Showcasing a one of a kind floorplan in Tower 5 of Yarra’s Edge, 235 sqm (approx.) of total space, and a wonderful northerly aspect allowing for magnificent views of the CBD, Yarra River, and beyond, this impeccable three bedroom, two bathroom apartment is one of the residential jewels of the Docklands precinct.
This 35th floor stunner truly needs to be seen to be believed. The immense central lounge and dining zone is flooded with natural light and has more space than you’ll know what to do with. Included in this huge central area is the chef's kitchen which delivers quality stone surfaces, large island bench, and full stainless steel Miele appliances.
The enormous balcony has access points from the main living and dining zone and two of the bedrooms, and is absolutely spectacular to soak in the breathtaking city and river views over summer dinners and New Year’s Eve fireworks. Back inside, the master bedroom fits in with the spacious theme of the apartment while also promising a double vanity ensuite, meanwhile the two other bedrooms are located on the other side of the residence for privacy and are right near the sleek bathroom.
Further extras include a separate laundry room, ducted heating and cooling, secure intercom, 2 secure car spaces, and access to RekDek which includes a gym, pool, spa, steam room, and sauna. The Yarra’s Edge is a highly desired area for Docklands owner-occupiers, with a position right near South Wharf Promenade, DFO shopping, Crown Entertainment Complex with world class restaurants, Southbank Promenade, Victoria Harbour precinct, and public transport.

Description:
Convenience, Class, and Beautiful Marina Vistas
The perfect blend of space and style matched by stunning marina views and a location in the Yarra’s Edge precinct, this tantalising two bedroom, two bathroom apartment promises a Docklands lifestyle to savour.
The northerly views are one of the first things you’ll notice when stepping inside this 11th floor retreat. The tranquil marina and further out to the Docklands are all within your sight and best enjoyed out on the generous undercover balcony, which is easily accessed via the spacious lounge and dining zone.
Whether preparing breakfast, lunch, or dinner, the stone kitchen never fails to impress with a moveable island bench and Smeg stainless steel appliances. The master bedroom boasts its own private balcony along with a walk-in robe and ensuite, meanwhile the other bedroom features a BIR and has access to the main balcony.
Other features include the central bathroom with European laundry, ducted heating and cooling, secure intercom, secure car space, and access to RekDek incl. gym, pool, spa, steam room, and sauna. Walk to South Wharf Promenade with restaurants and bars including Meat Market, The Boatbuilders Yard, The General Assembly, and Plus 5 Bar. You’re also close to DFO shopping, Crown Entertainment Complex, and public transport including Southern Cross Station.

Description:
Standout Docklands Pad with an Enormous Balcony
With highlights that include a generous full-length balcony enjoying superb views plus an open living zone that is bathed in natural light, this appealing one bedroom apartment in the Yarra’s Edge precinct is an outstanding entertainer.
This 24th floor dwelling is sure to catch the eye of owner-occupiers and smart investors who are looking to dip their toes in the Docklands property market. The expansive balcony is truly the highlight of the apartment, with an amazing amount of space and marvelous views including glimpses of the CBD and out towards Port Phillip Bay.
Full windows dominate the airy lounge and meals hub, while a gourmet kitchen will have you wanting to always eat in with its stylish stone benchtop, sleek glass splashback, and stainless steel appliances. The spacious bedroom enjoys a great corner position allowing for sensational views (also has balcony access), while further appreciate the pristine bathroom, separate laundry, ducted heat/cool, video intercom, secure car space, and access to RekDek incl. gym, pool, spa, steam room, and sauna.
Enjoy all the amazing amenities and attractions of the wonderful Yarra’s Edge area. South Wharf has great eateries and bars from the Thai flavours of Bangpop to an abundance of beer and bratwurst at Munich Brauhaus. You’re also very close to the world class Crown Entertainment Complex, DFO South Wharf, Capital City Trail, Polly Woodside, Spencer Street trams, and Southern Cross Station.

Boasting fantastic westerly views all the way down Yarra River and South Wharf, this coveted two bedroom, two bathroom apartment in Flinders Wharf sets the bar for considered and stylish Docklands living.

There is so much to like about this delightful two bedroom apartment situated on the 28th Floor of Tower 1.
From the spectacular, panoramic, never to be built out views across the Bay to Portarlington and the Mornington Peninsular and to the west along the Yarra River across the Docklands precinct and Bolte Bridge.

Two bedroom apartments in Lorimer Street in this price range are very hard to find, particularly with views like this, we suggest you inspect very early to avoid disappointment.

Description:
GRAND HERITAGE CHARM
The moment you enter the foyer you will be in scantly taken by the magnificence of old world charm. Amid the 19th Century, Victorian architecture is this apartment. The discerning buyer can expect the very best of quality in this apartment located on the 6th Floor in Melbourne’s grandest building, brimming with charm and character. The building was originally built in 1893, and was refurbished in 1996 to accommodate a mix of serviced and residential apartments. The apartment features a well-appointed kitchen with quality appliances, generous bathroom, a 4 metre ceiling height and floor to ceiling double glazed windows for an abundance of natural light leading out onto a balcony overlooking the CBD. Services include an indoor swimming pool, spa, sauna, gymnasium, caretaker, BBQ area and tranquil gardens as well as the adjacent Piano Bar restaurant and cafe. Located only a stone’s throw away from all of the amenities the city of Melbourne has to offer including Southern Cross Station, Southbank promenade and the Crown Casino complex just to name a few. Don’t miss out on this luxurious apartment.

Description:
A Docklands lifestyle you’ll fall in love with
From the superb outdoor entertaining options which includes two separate balconies, to the marvellous modern style and open plan layout, this memorable two bedroom, two bathroom apartment on the 11th floor of the sought-after Boyd Tower is one not to be missed.
This contemporary Docklands retreat is truly an instant classic. Mesmerising Victoria Harbour views can be enjoyed from the generous main balcony, which is entered via the spacious main lounge and dining zone which is your home for relaxing both day and night. The stone kitchen in incorporated into the central hub and includes a breakfast bar, elegant cabinetry and stainless steel appliances including a dishwasher.
A 2nd private balcony belongs to the fantastic master bedroom which also comes with terrific storage and a private ensuite, while further enjoying a 2nd bedroom with BIR, well-appointed bathroom with beautifully tiled shower and bath combo, European laundry, ducted heat/cool, intercom, secure car space and access to a BBQ area, pool, gym and function room.
Enjoy a location moments to superb restaurants including Oscar’s Table, Renzo’s Bar, Mint-o-Mustard and Cargo. You’re also near an IGA supermarket, Etihad Stadium, The District Docklands and Docklands Drive trams.
Please contact Thomas Tregonning on 0413 317 304 to arrange an exclusive viewing.

Description:
Sensationally Stylish and Super-Sized
Seize the chance to own one of Victoria Point's most unique listings! This dual key 2 in 1 apartment has access to a modern and spacious one bedroom retreat as well as a stylish studio residence both with their own entries. Perfect for investors as well as owner-occupiers, you're near Etihad Stadium, Bourke Street eateries, Docklands Park, trams, and Southern Cross Station.
Accommodation: Located on the one title but split into two separate apartments, this opportunity is incredibly rare. Buyers have the chance to rent out both properties for exciting returns (currently returning over 6.6% ROI!), while there is also the option to live in one of the properties and rent out the other! The one bedroom property is a picture of style and class, and features a generous main living and dining zone, stone kitchen with stainless steel appliances, undercover balcony with exceptional views of the CBD, Port Phillip Bay, and Docklands Park, bedroom with a built-in robe, and a chic bathroom with concealed laundry. The studio enjoys the same modern charm along with a relaxed living/sleeping area, stone kitchen, designer bathroom, European laundry, and a balcony with the same views. Don't miss this terrific Victoria Point prospect!
Features: Secure car space, ducted heating and cooling in both apartments, secure intercom, on-site building manager, access to a gymnasium.

Description:
Docklands alfresco space in stunning entertainer
Destined to impress those who love entertaining thanks to an immense courtyard area that will be a prime location for meals and drinks when the warmer weather kicks in, this unique two bedroom, two bathroom terrace apartment is literally steps to the scenic waters of Victoria Harbour.
The alfresco courtyard which measures 60 sqm approx has direct access to the beautiful communal gardens as well as a pool, gym and function room on the same level. Inside, you’ll appreciate the size and style of the relaxed lounge and dining zone which has direct access to the outdoor space, while passionate home cooks will benefit from a fantastic kitchen with stainless steel Smeg appliances.
Both bedrooms also have access to the courtyard including the large master bedroom which comes with a private ensuite. Further embrace a sleek bathroom, concealed laundry, reverse cycle heating and cooling, secure intercom, secure car space and a share of the Palladio recreation facilities.
Make the most of the popular NewQuay Precinct location where you’re seconds to restaurants including Woolshed, Solidaire, Fish Bar, and Medici Docklands. You’re also near IGA X-press supermarket, The District Docklands, Etihad Stadium and a multitude of trams.
Please contact Thomas Tregonning on 0413 317 304 to arrange an exclusive viewing

Description:
The Podium is Within Reach!
Located in the award winning Watergate residential complex, this low rise home among the tree tops has the most tranquil outlook around. Cosy and private, this apartment will suit a buyer looking for peace and quiet.
As you enter the apartment you will appreciate the stylish kitchen with white stone benchtop and white cabinetry. Stainless steel appliances include a gas stove top, oven and a dishwasher.
Open plan dining and living area adjoins the full length balcony set along lush greenery.
To the left of the apartment are two large bedrooms. Both bedrooms with mirrored BIR’s, main includes ensuite with 2nd bedroom sharing the central tiled bathroom.
Additional features include ducted reverse cycle heating and cooling, secured carpark, onsite manager with security entrance, floor to ceiling double glazed windows and cross flow ventilation.
Recreational facilities consist of a fantastic 3 lane heated swimming pool, spa, sauna, gymnasium and a residents lounge.
Centrally located in the heart of the Docklands makes it convenience plus. Walking distance to Woolworths, Australia Post Office, Library at the Dock, Southern Cross Station, superb cafes and eateries. Free Tram Zoned, easy access to the freeway and a short stroll into Melbourne CBD.
